[Data by country, area, or territory for 10 Aug 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20AUG10_1628709928.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 37.6% of daily case numbers and 22.3% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 78.92 million cases. The USA reported over 156 000 cases over the last 24 hours followed by Brazil (13 893). Seven additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, while 7 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 19.2% of daily case numbers and 15.0% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 61.56 million cases. Many countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Belgium, Sweden, Switzerland (7 cases), and Kazakhstan, among others. A total of 13 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, and an additional 10 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 11.9% of daily case numbers and 10.6% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 13.23 million cases. Iran reported the highest number of cases (40 808) over the last 24 hours, followed by Iraq, Morocco, Pakistan, Libya, and UAE. Lebanon, Saudi Arabia, Kuwait, and Jordan reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 4.0% of daily case numbers and 6.5% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 5.17 million cases. Botswana (8197) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours followed by South Africa. Algeria, Kenya, Mozambique, Zimbabwe, Eswatini, and Rwanda, reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Cameroon, Uganda, Ghana, and Congo, among others, did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 9.6% of daily case numbers and 7.9% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 5.01 million cases. Malaysia, reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 17 000 cases), followed by Japan, Viet Nam, Philippines, South Korea, Mongolia, Fiji, and Cambodia.

- The South East Asia region reported 17.7% of the daily newly reported cases and 37.7% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 39.37 million cases. Indonesia is dominant reporting over 32 000 cases over the last 24 hours, followed by India (28 204), Thailand (19 843), Bangladesh (11 164), Myanmar (4434), and Nepal (3194). Additionally, Sri Lanka and Maldives have not reported any cases in the last many days.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 10 Aug 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

